What is JavaScript?
  JavaScript is a programming language used to make web pages interactive and dynamic. It enables features such as event handling, DOM manipulation, API integration, form validation, and real-time content updates.

Features
  - Dynamic and interactive web pages
  - DOM manipulation
  - Event handling
  - API integration using Fetch API
  - Asynchronous programming (Async/Await)
  - Cross-browser support
  - Lightweight and fast

Components
  - Variables
  - Data Types
  - Operators
  - Functions
  - Objects & Arrays
  - Loops & Conditional Statements
  - Events
  - DOM Manipulation
  - Fetch API
  - Async/Await

Advantages
  - Makes web pages interactive
  - Easy to integrate with HTML and CSS
  - Supports asynchronous operations
  - Reduces page reloads
  - Large community and ecosystem
  - Cross-platform and browser compatible
  - Enables dynamic content rendering

Used in This Project
  - Fetching product data from the API
  - Rendering product cards dynamically
  - DOM manipulation
  - Displaying product images, titles, prices, and ratings
  - Handling API responses and errors
  - Creating an interactive user experience
